{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1629197700,"nonce":"YAjHbDaMtBdvmdG4YYfC7kDUY2I=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU5NzI1NTgwNjk=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3882","origin":"github"},"title":"ENA upload tool: handling of run input data","message":"From a user-reported error message at least, it seems that the ENA does not allow uploads of uncompressed fastq files:\n\n\u003e In run, alias:\"run_1_0_0_20210817_11:09:41\", accession:\"\", In filename:\"ONT_sequencing_file\", filetype:\"fastq\". Invalid file suffix for file \"ONT_sequencing_file\". File compression is required for file type \"fastq\". Supported compression formats are: BZIP2, GZIP with file suffixes: .bz2, .gz.\n\nThis would mean that if a user's data is really uncompressed in Galaxy, the *ena_upload* wrapper should probably compress it to .gz on the fly?\n\n\nA second issue is that currently the wrapper handles addition of a proper file suffix to dataset names only for pe collection input, but not for individual files - https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/474777450e3f847cb9badb020b56469f226546da/tools/ena_upload/ena_upload.xml#L77 and onwards.\nMy suggestion would be to add `.fastq.gz` or `.fastq.bz2` to the filenames to be submitted depending on the dataset type.\n\nIn addition, it could be helpful, both for pe collections and other input, if the tool could check whether the filename already ends in a proper suffix before appending one to avoid submitted filenames like `mydata.fastq.gz.fastq.gz` or `mydata.fastq.fastq.gz`. To make this more controllable by the user, maybe add an option \"Add file suffix to dataset name for submission\"?","files":null}]}